    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"not gone yet\" doesn't mean much when you know the end is coming. it just makes the waiting feel more painful. it feels like we're just clinging to things that don't have any real meaning. if the end is inevitable, why even fight to hold on to these memories? it feels more like a burden than anything else.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
